description: Table showing how many secondary schools less than 25 per cent. of pupils achieved (a) five A*-C grades at GCSE or equivalent and (b) five A*-C grades at GCSE or equivalent including English and mathematics in each local education authority in (i) 1997 and (ii) 2006; (2) in how many secondary schools 70 per cent. or more pupils achieved five A*-C grades at GCSE or equivalent in each local education authority in (a) 1997 and (b) 2006.
